value.0: Raphaël always seems to be taking account of supplies and sales for the bistro. He watches anyone who comes down to the cellar closely, ensuring no one tries taking anything. He appears to be about the same age as Mathéo and bears quite the resemblance. It is quite clear he is the patriarch's younger brother by only a few years.
A book in the hand is worth two on the shelf!

"Black and White, Dark and Light, see me not, within your sight."

Extremely rare, master smiths of far away notions copied the design from weapons taken from fallen Kara-Turan soldiers. The unusual weapons were carried by high ranking court assassins, and those that knew the meaning of the blade, and saw it drawn, usually did not live long enough to tell about it. Imbued with both forces of life, there is a balance to the blade that slips in, unnoticed, until it is too late.

A painting of Lilou Beauchêne, the matriarch of the Beauchêne family. She looks quite young in this piece. Her chocolate-brown hair is rich and silky, her lips a delicate pink. There is just a touch of sorrow in her deep blue eyes.

It is an old painting, but appears to be lovingly maintained.
